# MarkFlow API Testing
# Use this with VS Code REST Client extension or copy to Postman

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@workspaceId = REPLACE_WITH_WORKSPACE_ID
@noteId = REPLACE_WITH_NOTE_ID
@folderId = REPLACE_WITH_FOLDER_ID

### 1. Get all workspaces
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Create a new workspace
POST {{baseUrl}}/workspaces
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Workspace via API",
  "description": "Created through API testing",
  "isPersonal": false,
  "settings": {
    "theme": "dark",
    "defaultView": "split"
  }
}

### 3. Get notes for a workspace
GET {{baseUrl}}/notes?workspaceId={{workspaceId}}&page=1&limit=10
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Create a new note
POST {{baseUrl}}/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Note via API",
  "content": "# Hello from API\n\nThis is a test note created via the API.\n\n## Features\n- **Bold text**\n- *Italic text*\n- `Code snippets`\n\n### Math Example\n$E = mc^2$\n\n```javascript\nconsole.log('Hello, MarkFlow!');\n```",
  "workspaceId": "{{workspaceId}}",
  "folderId": null,
  "tags": [],
  "isPublic": false
}

### 5. Get a specific note
GET {{baseUrl}}/notes/{{noteId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Update a note
PUT {{baseUrl}}/notes/{{noteId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Test Note",
  "content": "# Updated Content\n\nThis note has been updated via the API!\n\n## New Section\nAdded some new content here.",
  "isPublic": true
}

### 7. Get folders for a workspace
GET {{baseUrl}}/folders?workspaceId={{workspaceId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Create a new folder
POST {{baseUrl}}/folders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "API Test Folder",
  "workspaceId": "{{workspaceId}}",
  "parentId": null,
  "color": "#f59e0b",
  "icon": "folder-plus"
}

### 9. Get tags for a workspace
GET {{baseUrl}}/tags?workspaceId={{workspaceId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Create a new tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/tags
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "API-Test",
  "color": "#8b5cf6",
  "workspaceId": "{{workspaceId}}",
  "description": "Tag created via API testing"
}

### 11. Delete a note
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/notes/{{noteId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 12. Search notes
GET {{baseUrl}}/notes?workspaceId={{workspaceId}}&search=test&page=1&limit=5
Content-Type: application/json 